ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Aha! The profile creation failed with `"Profile already exists"`. The
backend returns 400 because the user already has a profile row in the database (
created during user registration in `findOrCreateUser`).\n\nLooking at the backe
nd `auth.service.ts`:\n```typescript\nif (!user) {\n    // create user\n    cons
t profile = this.profileRepo.create({\n        user_id: userId,\n        is_comp
lete: false,\n    });\n    await this.profileRepo.save(profile);\n}\n```\n\nSo w
hen the user was first created, a profile row was inserted with `is_complete: fa
lse`. Then when the mobile app calls `POST /users/me/profile` (createProfile), t
he backend rejects it because the profile already exists.\n\nThe mobile app shou
ld be calling `PATCH /users/me/profile` (updateProfile) instead of `POST` (creat
eProfile) when the profile already exists!\n\nLooking at the `ProfileBloc._onSav
eProfile` method:\n```dart\nFuture<void> _onSaveProfile(...) async {\n    emit(c
onst ProfileLoading());\n    try {\n      final profile = await _profileReposito
ry.createProfile(event.request);\n      emit(ProfileComplete(profile));\n    } o
n Exception catch (e) {\n      emit(ProfileError(e.toString()));\n    }\n}\n```\
n\nIt ALWAYS calls `createProfile` (POST). But if the profile already exists, it
should call `updateProfile` (PATCH).\n\nThis is a **product bug** in the mobile 
app - the ProfileBloc doesn\'t handle the case where the profile already exists.
\n\nWait, but looking at the `ProfileSetupPage`, when `ProfileError` is emitted,
it should show a SnackBar:\n```dart\nlistener: (context, state) {\n    if (state
is ProfileComplete) {\n        context.go(\'/home\');\n    } else if (state is P
rofileError) {\n        ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar(\n           
SnackBar(content: Text(state.message)),\n        );\n    }\n}\n```\n\nBut the `s
etup.yaml` flow passed! It didn\'t fail. That means the flow didn\'t assert that
the profile was saved successfully or that navigation to home occurred. It just 
tapped "完成" and finished.\n\nSo `setup.yaml` is a **false positive** - it pass
es even though the profile save failed.\n\nThis is a flow issue AND a product bu
g:\n1. **Product bug**: ProfileBloc always uses POST to create profile, but for 
existing users (who already have a profile row), it should use PATCH.\n2. **Flow
issue**: `setup.yaml` doesn\'t verify successful profile completion - it just ta
ps "完成" without asserting navigation to home or checking for error SnackBars.\
n\nBut I can\'t fix the product bug (can\'t modify apps/). I CAN fix the flow to
be more robust, but it will still fail if the underlying product bug isn\'t fixe
d.\n\nActually, wait - can I modify the flow to handle the existing profile? No,
because the bug is in the app logic.\n\nLet me look at the backend profile contr
oller to see if there\'s a `createProfile` endpoint that should handle this case
.',
