ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. **Backend creates an empty p
rofile** when the user registers (`findOrCreateUser` in auth.service.ts creates 
a `UserProfileEntity` with `is_complete: false`).\n2. **Mobile app calls POST /u
sers/me/profile** (createProfile) in `ProfileBloc._onSaveProfile`.\n3. **Backend
rejects** with "Profile already exists" because the profile row already exists.\
n4. **Mobile app should call PATCH** instead when the profile already exists, or
the backend should allow POST to update an incomplete profile.\n\nThis is a **pr
oduct bug** - the mobile app\'s profile save logic doesn\'t handle existing inco
mplete profiles.\n\nBecause of this bug:\n- `profile/setup.yaml` is a false posi
tive - it passes but the profile isn\'t actually saved\n- `matching/swipe_recomm
endations.yaml` and `matching/view_match_list.yaml` fail because the user still 
has an incomplete profile and gets redirected to profile setup instead of home\n
\nNow, I can\'t fix the product bug, but I should report it. However, I can stil
l try to make the tests as meaningful as possible.\n\nFor `profile/setup.yaml`, 
I should add assertions to verify successful completion (e.g., assert navigation
